    "analysis": "Trace error_rate series for the candidate services are flat at 0.0 both globally and inside the incident window, so traces do not show elevated error rates. Metric-level analysis across the five candidate services showed many (cmdb_id, kpi_name) pairs with occasional breaches above global P95 and below P05 within the incident window, with mem spikes common and an extreme global P95 diskio for ts-order-service noted earlier. To localize the root cause we need to identify which component-KPI shows the most significant and sustained deviation (magnitude and consecutive duration) above its global P95 during the incident window — these faults are the likely root causes per the fault-identification rules. The next step is to quantify severity per (cmdb_id,kpi) by comparing the in-window extrema and streak lengths to the precomputed global P95 thresholds.",
