{
    "analysis": "Previous steps computed global thresholds and inspected metric anomalies for the five candidate services. Key findings: (1) ts-order-service shows the most significant user-impacting anomalies — large latency spikes (latency-90 ratio ~19x) with earliest breach at ~2024-01-24T01:18:00+00:00; (2) CPU spikes on ts-train-service and ts-travel-service (ratios >2) are present but less extreme for user latency; (3) disk I/O had elevated P95 on ts-order-service and ts-auth-service but with smaller ratios (~1.05–1.11); (4) trace error_rate features were flat (global P95 = 0) and therefore not informative. According to the workflow, next we must use traces to verify whether ts-order-service is the downstream faulty service in call chains (i.e., confirm it is the most downstream faulty service) and to see trace-level latency/duration signals for ts-order-service during the incident window. This will help confirm root-cause component versus collateral anomalies on other services.",
